Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.65,0:00:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,[music]\Nbe
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.20,0:00:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,[music]\N[music]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.84,0:00:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,on.\N[music]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.60,0:00:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,He [singing] be\N[music]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.71,0:00:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,>> [music]\N>> song.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.39,0:00:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Give me [music and singing]\N[music]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.52,0:01:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The difficulty with beauty\Nis that you can't function.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.40,0:01:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It totally wipes me out.\NGoing over Mingus Mountain this week,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.79,0:01:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the trees have been so beautiful.\Nalong one curve there's a tree in
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.24,0:01:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,stunning yellow. It stands out there\Nlike the radiance of God just pulling
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.04,0:01:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you off the road and you have to pull\Nover the side. I mean it could cause
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.92,0:01:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,accidents all over.\NToday we're talking about
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.11,0:01:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,h\NGod imminent and God transcendent.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.60,0:01:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,That sounds very impressive doesn't it?\NI had to write something for the
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.88,0:01:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,lecture.\N[laughter]
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.92,0:01:54.47,Default,,0,0,0,,God damn it. And transcendent. Whoa.\NThat would get you into divinity school
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.47,0:01:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,as a thesis, right?\NI never had time to go to divinity
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.36,0:02:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,school. Well, at one time I wanted to be\Na unity minister.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.96,0:02:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And and now I give talks at unity\Nchurches
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.72,0:02:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and and sermons at unity church. So I\Nsaved myself all that trouble again.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.96,0:02:28.68,Default,,0,0,0,,[laughter]\NWe won't talk about theology today
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.68,0:02:34.87,Default,,0,0,0,,[clears throat]\Nexcept maybe an occasional reference.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.87,0:02:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Those who are interested in theology,\Nyou'll find that the Encyclopedia
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.28,0:02:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Britannica under theology is stunningly\Nbrilliant.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.36,0:02:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,really excellent. If you want a review\Nof theology throughout the ages, the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.64,0:03:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,encyclopedia is really quite good.\NGod imminent means the realization of
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.16,0:03:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the source of one's own existence\Nradiating forth
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.28,0:03:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,as your beingness.\NTraditionally called realization of the
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.92,0:03:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,self.\NRealization
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.72,0:03:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,is sort of the right word but not\Nactually.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.44,0:03:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What happens is more a recognition.\NIt's more that everything you've seen in
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.44,0:03:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,a familiar way\Nnow you see it as a radiance of its
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.48,0:03:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,essence.\NIt's like revealed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.31,0:03:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's recognized. You recognize yourself\Nas all that exists, as the essence of
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.76,0:03:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,all that exists.\NAlthough it's a realization, it's really
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.48,0:03:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,a recognition.\NIt's also a remembrance because as it
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.95,0:04:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,shines forth, one wonders how one could\Nhave forgotten that [laughter]
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.64,0:04:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,some terrible insanity must have\Novertaken you
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.64,0:04:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that you've forgotten who you are. How\Ncould that be? It's a wonderment.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.72,0:04:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And that you were okay all along, all\Nthe lifetimes that you worried about
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.60,0:04:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,everything was ridiculous.\NYour survival is guaranteed
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.36,0:04:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,because that which is the essence of\Nlife has neither beginning nor ending.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.84,0:04:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Our\Ncountry is a theocracy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.68,0:04:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It's theist. No, it's not a theocracy.\NI'm sorry. It's theistic but not a
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.16,0:04:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,theocracy.\NThe fact that it's theistic bothers some
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.16,0:04:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,people\Nand I suggest they just ignore it and go
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.24,0:05:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,about their business,\Nwhich is what most people do in the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.08,0:05:05.75,Default,,0,0,0,,course of the day anyway. So you don't\Nhave to make a big political opus about
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.75,0:05:10.47,Default,,0,0,0,,it.\NIf you don't like God on your money, you
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.47,0:05:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,can white it out. I guess\Nyou can use foreign money. You can
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.84,0:05:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,transfer your money into Frank to other\Nthings in
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.88,0:05:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,traditionally. Throughout all of time,\Nman has been theistic.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.56,0:05:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Man has sought the source of his\Nexistence,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.40,0:05:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,explanation for life,\Na context in which to place it. So man
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.60,0:05:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,has struggled throughout all of time.\NEven primitive tribes,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.36,0:05:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,worship maybe the god, they could see\NGod in the bear or in the reindeer. They
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.88,0:06:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,could see God in nature. But there was\Nalways this constant search for God.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.96,0:06:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And as man became more intellectually\Nsophisticated,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.96,0:06:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,he attempted to intellectually define\Nit.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.36,0:06:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And thus grew theology and religion.\NI am chairman of the International God
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.00,0:06:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Anti-Defamation League\Nand one of my projects is to defend the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.16,0:06:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,good name of God who has been bismerched\Nthroughout the centuries.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.56,0:06:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,He's been maligned as the great\Nperpetrator.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.24,0:06:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,[clears throat]\NIt's necessary therefore to refer to the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.44,0:06:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,map of consciousness [snorts]\Nso that we can figure out where God
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.12,0:06:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,must be. You see,\Nas we calibrated the levels of
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.96,0:06:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness, we went from the lowest,\Nmost destructive
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.68,0:07:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,uh the poisonous uh reptile\Nuh the political militant who blows away
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.28,0:07:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,thousands of innocent people. We come on\Nup through normal, healthy people,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.16,0:07:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,loving people,\Nand we come up to the top.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.75,0:07:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, it's necessary to remember that God\Nis at the top of the chart and not the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.00,0:07:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,bottom. [laughter]\NThat's all that's required.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.31,0:07:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't that seem simple? [laughter]\NHowever,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.52,0:07:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout time, there are forces that\Ntry to make make the map go in the other
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.68,0:07:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,direction,\Nand we see them in current society. 911
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.63,0:07:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,was the eruption of God is at this end,\Nfolks.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.00,0:07:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And this side in this end, we're going\Nto have a protest parade to remove God.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.36,0:07:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So the God God here is the source of\Nkilling all Americans and infidels and
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.44,0:08:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,God knows what all.\NThey knocked off 3,000. They've only got
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.84,0:08:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,300,000 to go. [laughter]\NThey get busy round the clock. They
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.59,0:08:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,can't keep up with the birth rate. So I\NI want to tell them their project is is
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.52,0:08:26.87,Default,,0,0,0,,limited in in expectation.\NHowever, God has traditionally
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.87,0:08:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,been depicted in a variety of extremely\Nnegative ways. When I say the great
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.59,0:08:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,perpetrator, that's precisely how God\Nhas been maligned. Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.91,0:08:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,In July, we went through\Nabout 18 statements about the true
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.83,0:08:50.95,Default,,0,0,0,,nature of God. And the entire class we\Ncalibrated whether it was true or false.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.95,0:09:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And we got unanimously\Nunanimous agreement on the nature of God
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.48,0:09:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,in a normal theistic society. Then\Nthe authority for government, for rule,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.12,0:09:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,for law, for logic,\Nfor social mores, for ethics
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.92,0:09:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,has been\Nthat God is the source of our existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.80,0:09:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Without it, in an atheistic society, you\Nhave chaotic rule by force.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.20,0:09:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You have the waring tribes.\NYou have the disorganization and chaos
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.00,0:09:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,of a communist society.\NWhat happens when God is not
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.20,0:09:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,acknowledged as the source of life is\Nyou end up with totalitarianism.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.24,0:09:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,A fascist dictator will take the place.\NThen millions of people will gather in
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.83,0:10:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the great squares and go sigh, sigh,\Nsigh.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.48,0:10:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And God is then at the bottom of the\Nchart. When God is put at the bottom of
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.12,0:10:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the chart, then godly powers are given\Nto the state.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.00,0:10:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,No ethics,\Nno basis for human behavior other than
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.24,0:10:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,force.\NSo the levels below 200 represent force
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.88,0:10:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,which as they go down become\Nprogressively
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.00,0:10:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,frankly demonic.\NThe levels as they go up become
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.32,0:10:46.39,Default,,0,0,0,,progressively frankly more heavenly.\NWe presume that people want to move up
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.39,0:10:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the chart to heavenly heavenly peace.\NThat's idiotic. [laughter]
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.00,0:11:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Most people do not want peace at all.\NThey ra would rather be right. They'd
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.51,0:11:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,rather be right than have peace, you\Nknow. Uhhuh.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.76,0:11:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Peace is is a threat to many people.\NThey say there's nothing happening
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.83,0:11:18.95,Default,,0,0,0,,around here. We'll turn on Eminem.\N[laughter]
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.95,0:11:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Then something's happening. All right.\N>> [laughter]
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.51,0:11:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Little tune t turn up the boom box in\Nthe car and drive down the street. Boom
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.36,0:11:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,boom boom boom boom boom.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.48,0:11:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Although peace is forever within you,\Nuh people uh are afraid of it. They're
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.44,0:11:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,afraid of being wiped out by the\Ninfinite presence. And so the ego keeps
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.24,0:11:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,up its endless chatter. it like holds\Noff God
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.95,0:11:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,uh as best it can.\NIt makes sense to hold off the God of
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.24,0:12:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,religion. I remember when I became an\Natheist, it was a great relief. Frankly,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.36,0:12:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I was a scrupulous\Nscrupulously religious
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.72,0:12:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,came like a burden.\NAnd I think I've told you before,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.39,0:12:24.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I used to dread Saturday afternoon when\Nyou went to confession and then Sunday
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.95,0:12:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,morning you went to communion and you\Nweren't supposed to have a sin sin on
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.63,0:12:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,your soul\Nand the sin was supposed to be like a
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.92,0:12:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,black spot on your soul. Well, I dreaded\Nthat. You imagine walking around God is
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.88,0:12:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,staring down at this black sin and this\Nblack spot on your soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.83,0:12:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see the fear of God then the fear\Nof God was the fear of punishment. Fear
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.24,0:12:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,of God as the great punisher,\Nthe great avenger of your dastardly
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.80,0:13:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,wrongs.\NYou got annoyed with your mother. That's
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.56,0:13:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,enough to bang.\NDear father, have you sinned? I got
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.36,0:13:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,angry at my mother. You can say 12 hill\Nof Marys and 13 [laughter]
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.72,0:13:16.95,Default,,0,0,0,,our fathers\Nyou're getting angry at your mother. So
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.95,0:13:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,God became sort of dreadful\Nscary
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.60,0:13:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and when I became an atheist\Nit was a great relief.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.72,0:13:35.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, you can see why ungodliness\Nor no godliness, not anti-godliness, but
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.83,0:13:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,just ignoring God\Nallows you greater freedom
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.20,0:13:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,because that depiction of God is the\Ngreat oppressor.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.83,0:13:52.39,Default,,0,0,0,,People who revolt against God are really\Nnot revoling against God. The revoling
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.39,0:13:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,of an image of God\Nas the dreadful great oppressor, the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.83,0:14:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,ultimate threat.\NJudgment day.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.68,0:14:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh sinner, beware. Oh, [laughter]\Njudgment day.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.04,0:14:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, how did all that come about? And\Nwhat is the truth? Huh? What is the
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.80,0:14:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,actual truth?\NThe exit truth is that man tries to
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.24,0:14:32.16,Default,,0,0,0,,develop an conceptual understanding of\NGod, theological truth as best he can.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.16,0:14:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The instrument that he uses to do that\Nhowever is the intellect.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.76,0:14:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So theology then is using an instrument\Nwhich calibrates in the 400s. We said
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.44,0:14:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,reason,\Nintellect, understanding,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.32,0:14:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,abstract meaning is the intellect.\NSo you might say theology is the attempt
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.24,0:15:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,of the intellect\Nto describe and understand that which
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.12,0:15:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,incomp is incomprehensible. [laughter]\NUh let's see. Theology is in the 400s.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.48,0:15:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist 420 440 450 460 4\NTheology generally runs around 460. The
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.12,0:15:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,theology in the encyclopedia bratannica\Ncalibrates it over 450 460
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.92,0:15:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,is pretty high. 450 460 is pretty high\Nunderstanding
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.27,0:15:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,from an intellectual viewpoint. Hm.\NIf mankind has been unable to fathom the
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.56,0:15:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,true nature of God through the\Nintellect, then he's done it through
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.16,0:15:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,emotion. He's done it through\Nimagination.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.32,0:15:53.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The primitive tribe watches the volcano\Nerupt and presumes there is a goddess of
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.51,0:15:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,the volcano.\NSo to make the volcano stop erupting,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.07,0:16:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,you sacrifice virgins.\NIn volcanic countries, they run out of
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.27,0:16:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,virgins after a while. [laughter]\NVolcano keeps going. They keep
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.88,0:16:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,sacrificing virgins. Whoa.\NThey also sacrificed. They rip out the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.19,0:16:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,heart of young men on the altar also. So\Nyou'll find that the calibration of the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.24,0:16:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Incas and people such as that was not\Nextremely high.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.92,0:16:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh we have permission to do the Incas\Nresist. The Incas were over 200 resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.00,0:16:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, ripping out the hearts of\Nmaidens
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.60,0:16:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,to a demonic God\Nis worshiping God as the demonic. God as
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.48,0:16:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the demonic. So the history of religion\Nthroughout all cultures has really been
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.04,0:17:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,emerging from the misconception of God\Nis really the ultimate demonic.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.32,0:17:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The God of the Old Testament is very\Nthreatening,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.60,0:17:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,very selective,\Nprone to jealousy,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.12,0:17:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,having his nose out of joint,\Ngetting peeled at people,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.12,0:17:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,having favorites,\Nmaking promises,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.60,0:17:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,contracts,\Npartiality, and exhibiting all the human
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.67,0:17:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the defects of the human ego.\NSo Freud, as we said,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.48,0:17:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,attacked that and said that\Nthe ancient gods are projections from
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.64,0:17:47.91,Default,,0,0,0,,the unconscious,\Nprojections of hatred and fear,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.91,0:17:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,primarily hatred and fear of father\Nfigures,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.08,0:17:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,the bad, wicked, threatening, terrifying\Nfathers projected onto God.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.03,0:18:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,He then concluded therefore God did not\Nexist which was an incorrect
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.36,0:18:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,nonsecrator.\NHe should have said the false gods do
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.44,0:18:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,not exist but he did not really\Naddressed address
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.88,0:18:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,a real god. It was not within his\Nprovince. As you remember Freud
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.40,0:18:21.03,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates at 499\Nwhich is means he took the intellect as
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.03,0:18:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,far as it can go. So he's not to be\Nfaulted for having failed at that level.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.00,0:18:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, his level of evolution was 499.\NAnd he made great contributions to the
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.55,0:18:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,relief of suffering.\NMany of Freud's teachings, we don't even
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.91,0:18:39.91,Default,,0,0,0,,recognize the Freud's teachings. They\Nbecame so accepted that they become part
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.91,0:18:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,of our culture, part of our\Npsychological understanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.67,0:18:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't watch the evening no news\Nwithout some concept from psychoanalysis
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.20,0:18:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,appearing.\NThe killer must had something go wrong
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.36,0:18:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,in his childhood. Yeah. He got born.\NThat's what got
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.20,0:19:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,He had some pretty bad karma and\Ncame out with a little defective neuron
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.48,0:19:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,new neuronal structure. That's what's\Nwrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.67,0:19:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Um they can't help it because the\Nneuronal structure is faulty. The
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.64,0:19:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,prefrontal cortex is faulty. Not because\Nbad things happened to them in their
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.36,0:19:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,childhood. Bad things have happened to\Neverybody in this room.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.24,0:19:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody gone through childhood without\Nanything bad happening to them? Let's
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.67,0:19:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,see your hands.\N[laughter]
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.00,0:19:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The embarrassing moments, the chagrin,\Nbeing falsely accused,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.32,0:19:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,being punished for something your sister\Ndid and you didn't do. I mean, there's a
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.00,0:19:48.83,Default,,0,0,0,,million things, right? Being ganged up\Non the way home and
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.83,0:19:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,[clears throat] given a bloody nose.\NEndless things happen to people.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.72,0:20:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,People, here's the misconception\Nis that bad things that are happening
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.60,0:20:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,now are due to bad things that happened\Nto you then. No, bad things happening to
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.84,0:20:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,you then is and now is all for the same\Nreason. Because bad things are always
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.00,0:20:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,happening to you because this karma is\Nstill operative.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.28,0:20:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The karma that gave you a lousy\Nchildhood is the same karma that pulls
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.55,0:20:24.08,Default,,0,0,0,,the trigger to see what it's like to\Nkill your classmates. It's all the same
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.08,0:20:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,karma.\NTherefore, to understand
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.55,0:20:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,reality, the pathway to enlightenment to\Nunderstand God both imminent and
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.60,0:20:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,transcendent.\NThe one thing we stress at the beginning
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.20,0:20:50.08,Default,,0,0,0,,of every lecture\Nis that the basic defect of the ego is
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.08,0:20:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,its belief in causality.\NThere is a this causing a that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.24,0:21:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, we know that all things are\Nbecoming
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.96,0:21:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,appearing to be that which they appear\Nout of the presence of divinity in this
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.12,0:21:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,instant.\NIt's out of the now.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.44,0:21:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,out of the now that this that you\Nwitness is arising. It is not out of the
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.84,0:21:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,then.\NAll things arise
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.03,0:21:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and express themselves\Nas the fulfillment of their karmic
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.91,0:21:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,potentiality\Nas it opens thusly.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.48,0:21:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It is not because it's caused by\Nanything anywhere else in time or place.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.48,0:21:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Unless you realize that you will always\Npresume that there is a me in ego that
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.15,0:21:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,is the cause of what's happening. You\Nwill always presume that there's a me
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.40,0:21:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,causing this decision. There's a me\Ndoing that a that action.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.60,0:22:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You cannot get over identifying\Nyour personal self with the ego unless
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.48,0:22:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you get beyond causality.\NTherefore, causality is the biggest
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.48,0:22:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,basis for the continuence of the belief\Nin the ego
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.67,0:22:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,self.\NEverything is happening spontaneously.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.36,0:22:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing causing anything else.\NThere is no thinker causing you to
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.15,0:22:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,think.\NThe thinkingness is happening of its
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.84,0:22:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,own.\NThinkingness has a life of its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.72,0:22:50.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Thinkingness doesn't even give a rap\Nabout you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.27,0:22:52.55,Default,,0,0,0,,[laughter]\NYou think you're thinking this is your
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.55,0:22:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,friend.\NLet's all do an experiment. Let's all
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.55,0:23:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,stop thinking when I say stop.\NWhen I say stop,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.64,0:23:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I want everybody to command their mind\Nto stop thinking. Stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.64,0:23:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-oh. Oh.\N>> [laughter]
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.08,0:23:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Oh. Oh.\NThe mind will go right on with it
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.28,0:23:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,thinkingness because it's thinkingness\Nis coming from itself. It's not coming
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.44,0:23:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,from a you. There's a you that decides\Nthat your mind is going to think. It
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.88,0:23:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,does that all by itself. Doesn't give a\Nrap about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.96,0:23:43.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's quite a downer, isn't it?\NYour mind doesn't even care about you
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.91,0:23:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,here. You thought your mind was your\Nbest friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.36,0:23:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It's your mind that's going to get you\Nout of the troubles in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.08,0:24:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see what happens.\NHere's a thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.64,0:24:10.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Where' the thought come from?\NYeah, I drew where it came from. Where
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.55,0:24:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,it came from is right here.\NNowhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.32,0:24:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Came from right here. Nothing.\NNothing
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.15,0:24:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,at all.\NThe thoughts come out of nothingness
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.67,0:24:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and looking for the self within. The\Npresence of God within
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.55,0:24:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,is that which is a priority to the mind.\NYou have to catch it right before it
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.15,0:24:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,thinks. Once it thinks, you're looking\Nat the thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.72,0:24:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to look and catch right be what\Nis it that exists right before the mind
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.96,0:25:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,starts to think.\NIt is continuously present.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.55,0:25:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It's continuously present.\NBut consciousness itself does not think.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.79,0:25:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness itself\Nis like space.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.40,0:25:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Space is not thinking. Space is not\Ndoing anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.08,0:25:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But it is out of the potentiality of\Nspace that the pageantry of life occurs
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.00,0:25:35.67,Default,,0,0,0,,allows it to be witnessed.\NThe only reason you can see cat
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.67,0:25:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,the only reason you can see cat is\Nbecome because it's coming out of no
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.79,0:25:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,cat.\NIt's because it's against the background
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.64,0:25:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,of nothing that you can see it.\NIf it was against the background of
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.24,0:26:12.01,Default,,0,0,0,,something,\Nyou can't can't see cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.01,0:26:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,[music]\NThe lectures we gave on the structure of
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.79,0:26:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,the ego\Nwere because through certain
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.15,0:26:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,understandings\Nthe ego begins to collapse.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.00,0:26:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,What one is seeking in so-called\Nself-realization
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.64,0:26:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,is\Nthe awareness of one's identity with
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.44,0:26:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that which exists\Nprior to thought. I am that which does
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.84,0:26:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,not think.\NThat which I am doesn't think at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.24,0:26:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,People say what are you going to talk\Nabout? I have the slightest idea. So, I
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.03,0:27:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,read the thing.\NI'll tell you how long I spend thinking
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.40,0:27:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,about what I'm going to say.\N110,000th of a second
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.00,0:27:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,from here to here is 110,000th of a\Nsecond.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.79,0:27:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,110,000 of a second is how long I got to\Nbelieve what I'm going to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.76,0:27:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It happens of its own.\NEverything happens spontaneously
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.12,0:27:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,as an expression of its essence.\N[snorts]
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.03,0:27:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The style of its expression is\Ninfluenced by karmic propensities.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.36,0:27:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why we spent a lecture on karma.\NAnother difficulty with the western
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.32,0:28:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,world especially\Nis mankind stumbles along not only with
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.39,0:28:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,illconceptions and misconceptions about\Nthe nature of divinity and therefore of
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.12,0:28:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,himself\Nbut he's got karmic bumps and grinds to
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.32,0:28:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,deal with on top of it. [laughter]\NWe said last time that the newborn
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.32,0:28:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the newborns you can calibrate their\Nlevel of consciousness the minute
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.76,0:28:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,they're born. In fact, the soul doesn't\Nenter the embryo till the third month.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.32,0:28:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no point mourning\Na miscarriage in the first, second, and
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.64,0:28:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,third month because there's nobody home\Nyet.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.39,0:28:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,builder builds the building. Only at a\Ncertain point can you move in.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.36,0:28:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah so\Nfrom that moment on however you can
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.84,0:28:59.27,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrate the level of consciousness of\Nthe entity the being potential human.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.27,0:29:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,How is it that one comes in with a\Ncalibrated level of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.88,0:29:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,already?\NYou haven't even had a human life yet to
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.32,0:29:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,the\Nto the average understanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.12,0:29:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because this human life is just a\Nsequence.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.03,0:29:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is prior to thinkingness is\Nawareness consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.55,0:29:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of the unmanifest\Ninfinite potentiality of God arises the
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.12,0:29:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,manifest.\NOut of the manifest arises
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.96,0:29:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness.\NOut of consciousness arises life.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.24,0:29:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore life itself is entrance is\Ndivinity expressed as beingness
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.60,0:30:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,as existence.\NLife
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.52,0:30:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,cannot be destroyed or killed. It can\Nonly change form.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.15,0:30:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like the law of conservation of\Nenergy or the law of conservation of
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.60,0:30:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,matter. The law of the conservation of\Nlife is that you can
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.36,0:30:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,force life to move from this form to\Nthat form,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.08,0:30:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,but you cannot destroy life.\NWe've said that in many ways and we've
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.44,0:30:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,expressed it in funny ways and esoteric\Nways.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.52,0:30:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We said when you swat a fly it doesn't\Nnotice it.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.64,0:30:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's re reaffirm\Nwhen you swat a fly doesn't notice it.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.44,0:30:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist. Goes right on flying. Resist. I\Ntold you it moves from physicality into
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.00,0:30:52.55,Default,,0,0,0,,its atheric body. Goes right on flying.\NAny of you have been out of body? You
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.55,0:30:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,realize that one minute you're laying in\Nthe sick bed in in the hospital. Next
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.64,0:30:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,minute you're sitting up in the room and\Nwatching everything that's happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.12,0:31:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You haven't got a problem in the world.\NNo pain, no nothing. No problem. Don't
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.03,0:31:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,have to go to the bathroom. All kinds of\Nadvantages. No taxes. You don't have to
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.20,0:31:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,get dressed. Don't have to get up, go to\Nbed.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.60,0:31:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,H.\NSo
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.00,0:31:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,the essence of God then is the infinite\Nunlimited context of the entire
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.79,0:31:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,universe.\NGod is the infinite context.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.36,0:31:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The infinite context which out of which\Nthe entire universe arises
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.72,0:31:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,is an absolute perfect karmic harmonic\Nbalance. The power of God is infinite
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.20,0:31:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,like a giant electromagnetic field. All\Nthat exists throughout any all of time
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.44,0:31:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,anywhere in the universe which is\Nconstantly expanding
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.24,0:32:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,is held in place\Nby this enormous electromagnetic field
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.72,0:32:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,of infinite power. Infinite power.\NOne of the first things that stuns you
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.84,0:32:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,when you reach a state called\Nself-realization
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.15,0:32:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,is the power is of such immensity that\Nno human imagination can even get near
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.72,0:32:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,describing it.\NNot only is the beauty incapacitating
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.72,0:32:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and stunning and overwhelming that you\Ncan hardly breathe,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.88,0:32:43.91,Default,,0,0,0,,but the power is so infinite.\NThe idea that anybody would challenge
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.91,0:32:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the power of God is so funny that it's\Nhysterical. It's so pathetic.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.36,0:32:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It's so pathetic. If you've ever gone to\Na huge power plant, one of the great
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.24,0:32:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,dams, and watch the great turbines\Ncoming out,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.12,0:33:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and watch the electric power pulsing\Nout, you know, it's so incredible.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.08,0:33:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Hundreds of thousands of volts.\NIf you just put a little hair like that
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.44,0:33:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,would fry you. [laughter]\NTherefore,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.44,0:33:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,those who hate God and oppose God are\Npathetic and comical.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.88,0:33:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,No such thing is even possible.\NThey exist in two different domains.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.00,0:33:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,This domain below here is is power.\NI mean is force and that above it is
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.60,0:33:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,power. Huh?\NYeah. Now power is not threatened by
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.15,0:33:56.79,Default,,0,0,0,,force. Power is not threatened by force.\NReality is not threatened.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.79,0:34:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what shocks people when they say,\N"Well, what about aren't you afraid of
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.88,0:34:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,war?" And I say, "War and peace all the\Nsame.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.32,0:34:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all the same thing.\Nhard to understand
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.59,0:34:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,because this is a world of appearance\Nand the manifestation of that which is
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.56,0:34:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,karmically necessary\Nto evolve spiritually. Therefore, this
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.28,0:34:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,is a perfect world.\NThere's no point to change one iota of
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.48,0:34:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,this world.\NYou tell me where else you're going to
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.44,0:34:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,undo your bad karma.\NYou think of all the cruelty. You look
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.56,0:34:48.87,Default,,0,0,0,,at the history of mankind. You think of\Nall the cruelty that has accumulated
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.87,0:34:54.63,Default,,0,0,0,,here.\NYou think of the karma of the people
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.63,0:34:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that put thousands of people to death in\Ngas chambers and torture them.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.72,0:35:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Inquisition. Good God.\NThe amount of bad karma that needs to be
