Dialogue: 0,0:59:51.68,0:59:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's better to have no God than a wicked\NGod. Better
Dialogue: 0,0:59:58.00,1:00:02.79,Default,,0,0,0,,to have no god than a wicked god. At\Nleast you got some space to breathe and
Dialogue: 0,1:00:02.79,1:00:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,live. Be a human being without\Nconstantly being beset with guilt and
Dialogue: 0,1:00:07.20,1:00:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,fear. Huh? So the god of guilt and fear\Nthen is the one
Dialogue: 0,1:00:13.28,1:00:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,that has been the nemesis of man. The\Nnemesis.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:21.76,1:00:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Those who have experienced the presence\Nof God in its unmistakable absolute
Dialogue: 0,1:00:25.68,1:00:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,certainty\Nwhich is infinite beyond all time.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:30.96,1:00:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no time in which there can be\Nanything different because that which is
Dialogue: 0,1:00:36.07,1:00:42.31,Default,,0,0,0,,the absolute is always and exists now\Nbeyond time. Therefore, it's not subject
Dialogue: 0,1:00:42.31,1:00:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,to time or to change or any modification\Nas it is now. but has been, always will
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.88,1:00:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,be,\Nwhich is just a verbalization.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:53.52,1:00:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You only have to know it one instant and\Nyou know it forever because that instant
Dialogue: 0,1:00:57.11,1:01:00.31,Default,,0,0,0,,is forever because in that instant\Nyou're outside of time and you're into
