Dialogue: 0,1:25:51.76,1:25:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,consequence, not an arbitrary one, not a\Nmoralistic judgmental one. It's
Dialogue: 0,1:25:56.88,1:26:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,automatic.\NEvery thought then is like a minute
Dialogue: 0,1:26:02.48,1:26:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,particle. 1 - 400 10 the minus 400\Nmillionth of a watt.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:14.23,1:26:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like a tiny particle that has a\Ncharge and a configuration. So if
Dialogue: 0,1:26:18.80,1:26:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,everything that ever existence ever\Nexisted radiates out at every instant
Dialogue: 0,1:26:27.04,1:26:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,an energy and this energy has a\Npolarity.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:30.56,1:26:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It either gravitates to the top of the\Nchart or the bottom of the chart.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:35.28,1:26:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It has a charge.\NSome charges are stronger than other
Dialogue: 0,1:26:39.84,1:26:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,charges.\NYou can say that's not fair.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:46.63,1:26:50.08,Default,,0,0,0,,But that's the charge in your head. You\Nknow,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:50.08,1:26:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,no, everything is innately and\Nabsolutely fair. Why? Because everything
Dialogue: 0,1:26:55.60,1:27:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,can only be that which it is. You can't\Nbe that which you are not.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:00.56,1:27:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Consequently, if you can only be that\Nwhich you are,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:06.48,1:27:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,then what occurs as a consequence of\Nthat is absolute perfection.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:14.63,1:27:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is charged this way\Ngravitates this way and this that which
Dialogue: 0,1:27:17.92,1:27:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,is charged this way gravitates this way\Nautomatically
Dialogue: 0,1:27:22.56,1:27:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,as the nature of the expression of that\Nwhich it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:27.52,1:27:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,What could be more divine?\NThat each thing only experiences that
Dialogue: 0,1:27:36.56,1:27:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,which is faded to itself.\NAt the same time, it has at all times at
Dialogue: 0,1:27:43.92,1:27:52.23,Default,,0,0,0,,hand a means of salvation from those\Nerrors that may have been made. Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:52.23,1:27:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The infinite mercy of God is that\Nthrough prayer, through divine
Dialogue: 0,1:27:56.63,1:28:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,intervention, the opportunity to\Ntranscend exists always
Dialogue: 0,1:28:08.88,1:28:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,at the depths of the pits of hell\Nbeyond all human imagination,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:17.28,1:28:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,but intuited and written about by Dante.\NIn the pits of the foreverness of hell
Dialogue: 0,1:28:25.84,1:28:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,which goes on through timeless eons\Na black despair
Dialogue: 0,1:28:32.56,1:28:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,of agony of the soul which cannot be\Ndescribed
Dialogue: 0,1:28:37.92,1:28:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,in the incredible pits of hell.\NThe voice said, "If there is a God, I
Dialogue: 0,1:28:44.96,1:29:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,ask him to help me.\N[sighs]
Dialogue: 0,1:29:01.44,1:29:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Then came forth oblivion.\NAnd then the disappearance of any person
Dialogue: 0,1:29:09.28,1:29:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and only the presence of the infinite\Nessence of all that is
Dialogue: 0,1:29:16.63,1:29:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,radiating forth as all existence is the\Nsource and essence of all of life.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:22.23,1:29:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Beyond all time, beyond all description,\Nbeyond all limitation, beyond all
Dialogue: 0,1:29:28.00,1:29:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,intreaty.\NSo
Dialogue: 0,1:29:38.63,1:29:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,it would seem that\Nsalvation as such then is available
Dialogue: 0,1:29:44.96,1:29:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,even at great depths.\NSo we'll go on to some
Dialogue: 0,1:29:52.32,1:30:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,other questions.\NI just want to say one thing about
Dialogue: 0,1:30:00.00,1:30:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual practice so I don't forget it.\NI was say why didn't I say something
Dialogue: 0,1:30:03.76,1:30:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,about spiritual practice\Nthat spiritual practice is something you
Dialogue: 0,1:30:09.12,1:30:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,do as often and as frequently as\Npossible
Dialogue: 0,1:30:13.44,1:30:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and the one that I recommend is not is\Nnot dissimilar from that recommended by
Dialogue: 0,1:30:20.08,1:30:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Ramana Maharshi\Nin that
Dialogue: 0,1:30:26.80,1:30:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,there is a constant letting goess\Nand a constant looking within it's It's
Dialogue: 0,1:30:32.00,1:30:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,a matter of focusing. Instead of\Nfocusing without, you focus within.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:36.96,1:30:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What is deciding that? What is\Nexperiencing that? If there's a self-
Dialogue: 0,1:30:41.44,1:30:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,evvaluation going, where is the\Nself-evaluation coming from? In other
Dialogue: 0,1:30:45.19,1:30:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,words, you're trying to get to the very\Ncore of consciousness itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:50.71,1:30:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And as one does that, it transforms\Neverything.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:56.15,1:30:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like suddenly the black and white\Nworld is turned on to technicolor and
Dialogue: 0,1:30:59.92,1:31:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,3D. You see it as you've never realized\Nit before. The essence of divinity
Dialogue: 0,1:31:06.15,1:31:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,shines forth as all of existence\Nand it paralyzes you for quite a long
Dialogue: 0,1:31:13.12,1:31:16.12,Default,,0,0,0,,time.
